Citation.sAbstract: Partial molar volume, ?v0, isentropic compressibility, s, and partial molar isentropic compressibility, deg 0 k of glycine betaine in aqueous and aqueous KCl or MgCl2 solutions have been computed using the experimental density and speed of sound data at temperatures, T = 288.15 318.15 K. The transfer partial molar volumes, tr?v0, and transfer partial molar isentropic compressibilities, trdeg 0 k, have also been evaluated using the experimental data.
